DialogueNode.dialogue: Hey Sharon. Mind if I asked you about something?
Does this have to do with that discrimination case you mentioned yesterday?
Yeah. . . I heard from another employee that Stan acted in a highly inappropriate manner the other day during a meeting. Could you tell me a bit about that?
It does. Is it true that Stan yelled at you during a work meeting the other day?
Oh goodness... You heard about that?
Yes... Stan blew up at me. I guess he wasn't satisfied with the quality of my work...
I don't know how comfortable I feel discussing this...
Sharon, I completely understand. You don't have to talk about anything you're not comfortable with. But just know that I only want to help make this office a better place for everyone.
I get that. It must be scary to open up about these things. I'd never force you to talk about something that would make you uncomfortable, but I want you to know that I'm on your side.
Wow, thank you so much for understanding Alex. I'm truly blown away by how much you care. Thank you for saying that.
You know what... I'll tell you what happened. It's true. Stan blew up at me. He told me that my hormones keep interfering with my work and that if I can't get a handle on my emotions I'd be fired.
He told me that my hormones keep interfering with my work and that if I can't get a handle on my emotions I'd be fired.
I don't even know what to say, Sharon. I am so sorry you had to experience that. I will certainly be confronting Stan about that.
Sharon, that is truly awful. Would it be alright with you if I were to confront Stan about this?
Well I certainly think Stan's attitude needs to change. Just... don't tell him I told you any of this, okay?
I promise you, your job is not at risk at all. We're going to sort this out as soon as possible. Thank you so much for your compliance and bravery.
